cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a P2P software framework and implementation of a P2P network. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of different transport layers such as TCP or UDP. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as the paper discusses the implementation of a small-world architecture. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses the routing algorithm used in the Symphony network. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is a possible category as the paper presents experimental results on the performance of the Symphony network.
